Let $x$ = batches of cookies and $y$ = batches of brownies.

**Objective function** (to maximize):
$$
 z = 3x + 4y \quad \text{(profit in dollars)}
$$

**Constraints:**
$$\begin{aligned}
 2x + 3y &\leq 12 && \text{(flour constraint)} \\
 x + y &\leq 5 && \text{(total batches constraint)} \\
 x &\geq 0 && \text{(non-negativity)} \\
 y &\geq 0 && \text{(non-negativity)}
\end{aligned}$$

The complete linear programming problem is:
$$
\boxed{
\begin{array}{ll}
 \text{Maximize} & z = 3x + 4y \\
 \text{subject to} & 2x + 3y \leq 12 \\
 & x + y \leq 5 \\
 & x \geq 0, \, y \geq 0
\end{array}
}
$$
